From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000052 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Julien Etienne <julien.etienne@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 18:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: mediatek: add disabled Gemini BMI160 candidate

The live Gemini vendor stack exposes BMI160-named clients at I2C1 0x68 and
0x69, but both vendor probes rewrite the Linux i2c_client address to 0x69.
The gyro path validates Bosch-family IDs and the accelerometer path reads the
BMI160 ID register; the electrical part has not been directly probed yet.

Describe one standard upstream BMI160 instance at the likely physical address
and keep it disabled. Do not guess supplies or interrupt wiring: the vendor
configuration reports no controlled sensor rail and the legacy clients use
polling. The direction-7 transform is the recovered board orientation and is
safe as metadata, but enabling this node still requires a direct ID, rail, and
runtime recovery test.

Signed-off-by: Julien Etienne <julien.etienne@gmail.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts
@@ -219,3 +219,19 @@
 		status = "disabled";
 	};
 };
+
+&i2c1 {
+	/*
+	 * Keep this candidate disabled until the physical ID, rails, and
+	 * interrupt/polling contract are verified on a recoverable image.
+	 * The vendor's logical 0x68 client is rewritten to 0x69 in probe.
+	 */
+	bmi160_candidate: bmi160@69 {
+		compatible = "bosch,bmi160";
+		reg = <0x69>;
+		mount-matrix = "0", "-1", "0",
+				       "-1", "0", "0",
+				       "0", "0", "-1";
+		status = "disabled";
+	};
+};
